<section xml:id="opening-the-task-editor-for-items-in-browsers" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                                                          xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                                                          xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <title>Opening the task editor for items in browsers</title>
  <anchor role="helpid" xml:id="testSpecificationViewContextId">Test Case Browser</anchor>
  <anchor role="helpid" xml:id="testExecViewContextId">Test Suite Browser</anchor>
  <para>
    Each Test Case, Test Suite and Test Job in a Project can be
    joined to a task in an external repository via a task ID
    (<xref linkend="working-with-external-task-repositories"/>). You can open the task for an item from the
    browser:
  </para>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Select the item whose task you want to open in the browser.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Right click and select:
      </para>
        
      <para>
        <emphasis role="menuPath">Open with</emphasis>--&gt;<emphasis role="menuPath">Mylyn Task Editor</emphasis>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        The task from the external repository will open in the ITE.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
  <para role="warning">
    If no repository has been defined for the Project, or the
    task ID does not exist, or the repository is not configured in
    the workspace, then the task will not open.
  </para>
</section>